Package: SpeTestNP
Type: Package
Version: 1.0.7
Date: 2021-03-25
Imports:
  np
Suggests: 
  pracma
Title: Nonparametric testing for linear models
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hippolyte", "Boucher", email = "Hippolyte.Boucher@outlook.com", role = "cre"),
    person("Pascal", "Lavergne", email = "lavergnetse@gmail.com", role = "cre"))
Maintainer: 
  Pascal Lavergne <lavergnetse@gmail.com>
Description: 
    The package has a single do-it-all function called SpeTest which
    returns the statistic and the bootstrap p-value of a nonparametric specification
    test. 5 tests are available: Bierens (1982), Zheng (1996), Escanciano (2006),
    Lavergne and Patilea (2008) and Lavergne and Patilea (2012). Bandwidth and kernel
    selections are available along with  many other options.
